Brazil, Mexico Want to Join MILA, Colombia’s Santos Says

-- B y   H e l e n   M u r p h y
-- 
2011-08-12T21:44:11Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-12/brazil-mexico-want-to-join-mila-colombia-s-santos-says.html
Brazil  and  Mexico  are interested in
joining the integrated stock trading exchange known as MILA,
Colombian President  Juan Manuel Santos  said in e-mailed comments
from the president’s  office .  The exchange, which began May 30, comprises Colombia, Chile
and  Peru . MILA allows cross-border transactions between the
three nations, creating  Latin America ’s second-biggest stock
market after Brazil.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Helen Murphy in Bogota at 
 hmurphy1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joshua Goodman at 
 jgoodman19@bloomberg.net  